The paper deals with algorithms for estimating moments in data streams, which is a classic problem in data structures (cs.DS). The algorithm uses techniques from information theory (cs.IT) to achieve space-optimal performance. The problem of estimating moments is also relevant to databases (cs.DB) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper uses machine learning techniques (cs.LG) to analyze the performance of the algorithm.
